subSubSection.paragraph:
The genus 

Squalus

has recently undergone intensive scrutiny and revision with, for example, 11 new species being described in 2007 alone (e.g., see 
Last et al., 2007d
), and with multiple species having been resurrected in the last several years (e.g., see 
Last et al., 2007d
; 
Ebert et al., 2010
). In our treatment of species in this genus, we have attempted to follow this new taxonomy as closely as possible.

The analysis included two samples of this recently resurrected (see 
Last et al., 2007c
) Indo-Pacific species, both of which were collected from voucher specimens deposited in the Australian National Fish Collection (GN4981 5 ANFC H 2609-07 and GN4982 5 ANFC H 4623-05). These specimens differed from one another by one base.

Three specimens of this newly described species (see 
White et al., 2007c
) were included
